'''''Sahukara''''' ({{lang-kn|ಸಾಹುಕಾರ}}) is a 2004 Indian [[Kannada language|Kannada]] romantic drama film directed by [[Om Prakash Rao]] and produced by K. Manju. The film stars [[V. Ravichandran]], [[Rambha (actress)|Rambha]], [[Shashikumar]] and [[Anu Prabhakar]] in the lead roles.<ref>[http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/1734/kannada/sahukara/cast.and.crew.htm Cast & Crew]</ref> Veteran actor [[Vishnuvardhan (actor)|Vishnuvardhan]] made a special appearance in the film.<ref>[http://www.vishnuvardhan.com/home.htm Vishnuvardhan film list]</ref> The film was a remake of the [[Malayalam]] film ''[[Thenmavin Kombath]]'' <ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2004/08/23/stories/2004082301590200.htm|title=The Hindu : Best of both|website=www.thehindu.com|access-date=2018-06-16}}</ref> starring [[Mohanlal]] and [[Shobana]] in lead roles. 

The film released on 24 September 2004 to generally positive reviews from critics<ref>[http://www.viggy.com/english/review_sahukara.asp Reviews from Viggy]</ref> and successfully screened for about 7 weeks in cinema halls.

